-### fexwrap
-
-> A janky temporary setup to run x86_64 Flatpaks (namely Steam) with FEX-Emu on aarch64.
-
-- Adrian: flatpak needs to know that it needs to download 2 different runtimes, and mount, how?
-  - Abderrahim: there is a script that exists - fexwrap https://codeberg.org/valpackett/fexwrap
-  - fexwrap would need to be on the host system
-  - it's a hack, but could have potential
-  - from fexwrap's perspective the native runtime is the host
-    - /app needs to be x86
-    - /usr most would be arm
-    - /usr/bin woudl be arm
-    - libraries would need to be both
-  - fex, thunk libraries, and the rest libs would be x86_64
-  - https://github.com/FEX-Emu/FEX/tree/main/ThunkLibs
-  - The extension could be:
-    - libraries
-    - fexwrap
-    - script that replaces the libraries with thunks?
-  - Flatpak would have to:
-    - know you're downloading wrong architecture
-    - use an extension then
-    - the app would need to be invoked by fex
